race.comment: PODARGONI (6) resumed in good order and then found the grade a bit rich at Flemington. He has more to give and is a third-up winner suited in this grade. In a top metro barn and draws to advantage. LENSMAN (9) made sharp improvement narrowly beaten at Cranbourne over 1400m. Jumps from the rail again and will strip fitter. Egan goes on and he has winning claims. YAM (5) was outgraded at Flemington 8-days ago but was an easy winner here prior. Has to drop back to a shorter sprint but has a handy 3kg claim and must be pleasing. VIANARRA (14) resumes and is good enough to feature if presented on song. Maps for the run of the race and the in-form Meech is engaged. STAR BUYER (4) has more to give and will find this easier than Caulfield Heath. Goes well second-up and the 3kg claim brings him into it.
